Day 4: Randomisation and Python Lists
# common python modules in askpython.com

# modules in python
# modules are files with the ".py" extension containing python code that can be imported inside another python program

# random module
# implement a random number python module into your code
import random
random_integer = random.randint(1, 10)
print(random_integer)
# write a program that can be used for heads or tails if you don't have a coin
import random
random_side = random.randint(0, 1)
if random_side == 1:
  print("Heads")
else:
  print("Tails")
